Trading bank staff in Wellington andAuckland voted to accept a 7.9 pct pay rise, ending any threatof strike action, the Bank Officers Union said.    Union president Angela Foulkes told Reuters that Wellingtonand Auckland staff are still unhappy with the offer butaccepted it because they could not have forced a higher offerwhen provincial union members had already accepted the 7.9 pct.    Provincial bank staff approved the offer at meetings lastweek but Wellington and Auckland workers had initiallythreatened to strike in support of a higher claim. REUTER&#3;